**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Attackers can inject newlines (`\n`) to create fake log entries that appear legitimate
- Forged logs can show successful admin logins, hide attack evidence, or implicate innocent users
- ANSI escape codes can erase previous log lines or corrupt terminal output
- Log aggregation systems (Splunk, ELK) may parse forged entries as real events
- Compliance audits become invalid when log integrity cannot be guaranteed

**SECURE VERSION**:

